channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Want to Support Conservatives in the Arts? ‘Arise’ by Glass Hammer Is a Great Place to Start
Biden caters to 'far-left' dark money groups with Supreme Court 'gimmick,' critics say
item.description: Critics say President Biden’s push to impose radical changes on the Supreme Court caters to the left-wing Democrat base from an administration that was once billed as "moderate."

item.title: Arizona's Hamadeh: Kamala Wants to 'Destroy' Country
item.description: Republican Congressional candidate Abe Hamedeh told Newsmax on Monday that voters "truly do" recognize how Vice President Kamala Harris is such a radical liberal, especially when it comes to immigration. Hamadeh has been endorsed by former President Donald Trump and seeking...

item.title: Could Swiss Style Fiscal Rules Work in the United States?
Crucial southwestern battleground holds Senate, House primaries today
item.description: The general election battleground state of Arizona is holding primaries that will set the stage for autumn showdowns that may determine control of the House and Senate.

item.title: Trump Speech in Nashville Delayed by Security Lapse
item.description: The Secret Service briefly delayed Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump from taking the stage at a conference in Nashville, Tennessee, over the weekend due to a security lapse, the New York Post reported Monday night.

item.title: 'Good Morning, General' - Intern From Kamala Harris' Attorney General Days Shares Eye-Opening Stories
9/11 terrorist fears Trump will be elected and execute him as lawmakers urge DOJ against French transfer
item.description: A dozen Republican senators reacted to a terrorist's plea for extradition by urging the White House and Justice Department not to allow him to live out his term abroad.

item.title: Unions Want Sen. Peters of Mich. to Be Harris VP
item.description: Sen. Gary Peters, D-Mich., is being pushed by organized labor to be considered as Vice President Kamala Harris' running mate, Axios reported.

item.title: NC Governor Roy Cooper Withdraws From Kamala's Veepstakes
The ‘weird’ campaign: The stunning difference between Harris and Vance coverage
item.description: Kamala Harris recently entered into the 2024 race and the media's coverage between the two tickets is starkly different, some say "weird."

item.title: Pastor Amanchukwu to Newsmax: Harris Exploits Her Racial Identity
item.description: Founder and president of IKNOWGOD.US, Pastor John Amanchukwu, voiced strong criticisms of Vice President Kamala Harris during an appearance on Newsmax on Monday, accusing Harris of manipulating her racial identity for political gain.

item.title: Canada Gooses: More Trouble Than Canada Mooses
Trump to attend National Association of Black Journalists Convention in Chicago
item.description: Former President Trump will participate in a discussion at the National Association of Black Journalists Convention in Chicago, Illinois, his campaign said.

item.title: N.C. Gov. Withdraws Name From Harris' VP List
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' list of potential running mates dropped by one Monday when North Carolina Gov. Roy Cooper took himself out of consideration to join the ticket of the presumptive Democrat presidential nominee.
